This paper involves the development of a machine learning model for predicting court decisions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), as the paper deals with text data. Additionally, the paper involves the use of AI techniques for predicting court decisions, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the security and privacy of legal data, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
